<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>User Management API</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        background: #f4f6f8;
        color: #333;
        padding: 30px;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: auto;
      }

      h1 {
        color: #007bff;
        border-bottom: 2px solid #007bff;
        padding-bottom: 10px;
      }

      p {
        font-size: 18px;
      }

      ul {
        margin-top: 20px;
      }

      li {
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }

      code {
        background: #eee;
        padding: 2px 6px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        font-family: monospace;
      }

      a {
        color: #007bff;
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
      }

      footer {
        margin-top: 40px;
        font-size: 14px;
        color: #888;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Welcome to the User Management API</h1>
    <p>
      This is a simple Express.js app that allows you to manage and filter user
      data stored in a JSON file.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>To view all users, go to <a href="/users">/users</a></li>
      <li>
        You can filter users by passing query parameters like:
        <ul>
          <li><code>?name=Ali</code></li>
          <li><code>?age=22</code></li>
          <li><code>?name=Ali&age=22</code> (for multiple filters)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        To add a user, send a <code>POST</code> request to
        <code>/users</code> with a JSON body (use Postman or similar)
      </li>
    </ul>

    <footer>Developed with ❤️ using Node.js and EJS</footer>
  </body>
</html>
